Text: Schoolgirl: \n Oh, wow! It's Raven!
One Year Later...
Schoolgirl: \n Raven! I'm your biggest fan!
Schoolgirl: \n Is that really her!?
Schoolgirl: \n It's Raven in the flesh! How cool!
Schoolgirl: \n Raven, you're amazing!
Schoolgirl: \n It's Raven!
Syd: \n HEEEY, Raven!
Syd: \n Later!
Patrol Auldnoir
I'll start over by the factory today.
Woman: \n Fight! Someone stop them!
Heya, heading out to \n patrol the town?
I was just getting ready \n to go now.

Syd, did you ever 
 figure out what 
 happened to that 
 kid who was king?
We found him. He was \n still alive, so we have \n him in custody.
But he somehow \n managed to vanish \n on us.

Hey, who would've 
 thought the day would 
 come when you'd 
 become the town's hero?

You've come a long way 
 from when "the raven 
 girl" struck fear into 
 people's hearts.
Hmph, guess \n people change.
Of course, that's what \n makes us human.
I heard the Banga fleet \n was coming today.
Guess they're gonna dock \n at the Downtown pier.
You should drop by, \n they'll be happy to see \n a familiar face.
Maybe I will. What about \n you, Syd?
I'll pass this time, \n have some stuff to take \n care of.
I'm busy hunting down a \n hard-to-find wine.
Does this hard-to-find \n wine happen to have a \n black cat on the label?
Excellent guess, Raven.
Tell Lisa and the others \n I said hi!
I will. And I hope you \n find that wine.
Hmph, guess I'd better break them up.
Break up the Fight
Schoolgirl: \n It's Raven!
Man: \n Thank goodness you're here!
Woman: \n Please, you've got to help!
Hmph, that's done.
Chaz: \n Miss Raven!
Looks like Pleajeune is next on the patrol route.
Patrol Pleajeune
Hm?
Thank you for your help \n keeping the peace.
We just got approved to \n deploy more officers in \n Auldnoir.
So you can leave this \n place to us!
You can't spend the rest \n of your life fighting \n crime.
You should go have a \n night out to yourself.

Maybe drop by that 
 fortune teller in 
 Pleajeune and ask if 
 love is in the cards.
Boss! She's a big girl, \n let her live her own \n life.
It sounds like my next \n stop is Pleajeune.
Y-Yes, of course.
After what happened, \n have you heard-
Nothing...
I see...
Is that Aujean down there?
I should go check on Eugie.
It's time to drop in on Aki.
Head to Pandora's Fortunes
Okay, time to take Pandora's advice and go downtown.
Head Downtown
Huh?
Is that Newt and Echo over there?
Hm?
Echo: \n Hey, isn't that one of the Banga airboats?

Hey, honey. You'd be 
 proud of Eugie, he's 
 nothin' like his old 
 man.
Let's celebrate. Is your \n glass ready where you \n are?
Aujean, having a drink \n with your wife?
Raven! I've got big \n news...
My boy Eugie made it \n into Arquebus Academy!
Congratulations, that's \n not easy.
If Kat were around, her \n jaw would hit the \n ground.
Yeah, I'll bet it \n would...
Where is Eugie? I'd like \n to congratulate him in \n person.
He's already over at the \n school, scopin' it out.
Okay, I'll head over \n there.
Make sure to tell Eugie \n to keep his nose to the \n books!
Head to Endestria
I might as well drop by Endestria, it's on the way.
Nothing out of the ordinary here...
Everything checks out here.
Everything's fine here.
Hey, Raven, out on \n patrol?
Yep, as always. I heard \n from your dad you got \n into the academy.
I figured you were all \n ready to take over his \n ice cream stand.
Nah, my friends set me \n straight. Got me to see \n studyin' was important.

School's supposed to 
 open your eyes and 
 expand your horizons. 
 Somethin' like that...
I always figured school \n would be borin', but I \n guess it's not all bad.
I'll keep that \n in mind.
My grandpa was the \n one who first turned \n me on to school.
Once I'm done studying \n here, I'm gonna head out \n and see the world.

Me, I'm gonna study hard 
 and become the president 
 of my own ice cream 
 company!
People'll be fallin' all \n over themselves for \n my premium wares.
I'm gonna make Pops \n proud! Just... Don't \n tell him I said that.
Good luck, and it'll be \n our secret.
Pandora welcomes you, \n Raven!
I'm here for my \n fortune.
Anytime! I'm guessing \n you want the usual.
Pandora, tell us the \n future!
Today's lucky spot is \n "Downtown."
Pandora, Raven wants to \n know about "the one \n she's waiting for."
Today's lucky spot is \n "Downtown." \n Today's lucky spot is-
Hmm, my Pandora's not \n feeling well.
Well, it's hard to \n ignore her advice. I'll \n try my "luck" downtown.
I'm sorry, you don't \n have to pay me for \n today.
Not charging me? Now I \n think you're the one \n that's not feeling well.
May peace and joy be \n with you, Raven.
And you're not the only \n one who's waiting...
Yunica, Permet... \n You're alive!
Everyone pulled \n through... \n Well, almost everyone.
What are you going \n to do now?
We stopped the invasion \n from the top of the \n world...
Hekseville doesn't need \n the Jellyfish special \n forces anymore.
Nevertheless, we'll \n continue to train...
We need to be ready if \n there's ever another \n threat.
Sea Wasp, \n Commander Yuri \n is calling us back.
Right. \n Come on, Sea Slug!
Roger that!
Oobie Oobie Oo!
Stop it, I just got her \n to sleep.
Newt, Echo! \n Long time no see!
Raven! Hey, you haven't \n seen the kid yet.
This is our daughter.
She's adorable. What's \n her name?

Alua. That's the name 
 the teller over at 
 Pandora's Fortunes 
 gave us.

The name comes from the 
 word "alpha," meaning 
 the beginning of 
 everything.
We fell in love with the \n name the moment we \n heard it.
Alua, huh? \n I like it.
It seems so unreal we \n can be together like \n this.
You saved us. \n Thank you, \n Raven.
And Kat.
And Lisa too.
She's doing a great job \n leading Hekseville.
She pulled us and Jirga \n Para Lhao together when \n we needed it.
We're hoping she gets \n elected mayor.
I'll let her know you \n said that.
I hope I run into you \n two, no, three again.

I heard from Syd that 
 the Banga fleet was 
 coming, I didn't know 
 you'd be coming with it.
Yeah, I've been so \n busy...
Lisa has to run two \n cities, she's swamped.

The people of Hekseville 
 think you're doing a 
 great job. Any plans to 
 run for mayor?

I don't care much for 
 titles. I just want to 
 do what needs to be 
 done.
Lisa, Raven, you're both \n doing so much. It's \n amazing.
Cecie, you're doing an \n amazing job yourself.
Gawan told me you were \n handling everything \n well.
You're the only reason I \n can stay away from Banga \n as long as I do.
Guess you've really \n grown into your \n new role, Cecie.
I always wanted to be \n strong and positive...
Like Kat.
Speaking of Gawan, are \n he and Misai around?
Yeah, they're helping \n out some of the traders \n on the other airboats.
Vogo and the others are \n here too, look.
Hey, Raven! How's life?
Good. And you haven't \n changed a bit.

We're doing great. You 
 can always rely on the 
 brothers of Sun 
 Shipping!
We take our business \n seriously.
Yes we do, Vogo.
Well, Vogo, maybe you \n have changed.
We need to get this \n cargo delivered on the \n double.
That's the one bound for \n the ship Gawan's on. \n I'll-
Leave it to me, I was \n going to see Gawan \n anyway.
Really? That'd help us \n out a bunch.
Gawan's over on an \n airboat docked at the \n small shipping pier.
Say, Raven, you still \n all by yourself?
You must miss her. You \n were always together.
It feels so quiet \n without her around.
You just have to accept \n the changes life brings \n and move forward...
Y-Yeah, exactly! \n Thank you for your \n help with the cargo!
Raven, is that you? \n It's been so long.
Looking for this? \n I brought it \n from Vogo.
Yes, yes I was! \n Thank you.
When I saw it was \n missing, I thought \n maybe I miscounted.
Growin' old, you can't \n depend on your memory \n like you used to.
Though I still remember \n a lot of things from \n when I was younger.
You know, I sometimes \n mistake Cecie for a \n young Lisa.
Funny, isn't it, Kat?
Raven.
Oh, right. Sorry, \n slipped there for a \n second.
It's okay, just take \n care of yourself, Gawan.
I will. You're a kind \n girl, strong too. But if \n you ever need to talk...
Come on by Banga \n Settlement anytime \n you want.
I will, thank you, \n Gawan.

Hey, lookin' good, 
 Raven! Been so long, was 
 wondering what you've 
 been up to.
Sorry, I've just been so \n busy with the patrols.

Admit it, you were just 
 worried you might stir 
 up some old memories 
 for us.
You got me.
You can't fool me. But \n you don't have to hide.
You never know, she \n might be out there, \n somewhere.
You really believe that?
I've accepted it. I keep \n her memory with me, \n but I've moved on.

Hey, I just said you 
 can't fool me. You don't 
 have to put on a brave 
 face.

What do you know about 
 what it's like to have 
 half of who you are torn 
 away from you?
I'm sorry, I shouldn't \n have said that.

I-I just have to believe 
 she's out there 
 somewhere, happy, living 
 life to the fullest.
Ah shoot, now you've got \n me tearing up.
Just... Stop by Banga \n more often, okay?
Thank you, I will. And \n thank you for worrying \n about me.
That's what \n I'm here for!
Here I am again... Even when I know it can't be her...
I should head over and say hello.
Head to the Mining Boat
Cecie: \n Hey, Raven!
Vogo: \n Oh come on, what's this doin' here!?
Lisa: \n What are you getting worked up about now?
Deliver the Cargo \n to Gawan
Vogo: \n Thanks for the help! Don't go droppin' it.
Gawan's over there.
Misai: \n Hey, Raven!
Misai? I haven't seen you in ages.
Was that...?
No one's here... But that voice, it sounded like...
Mother: \n Get back from there, it's dangerous and we have to go!
Son: \n But there was something down there. It might be a lost kitty cat!
A cat?
Mom: \n Sure, son, maybe it is, but we need to go.
Am I imagining things?
There it is again! It's coming from over there.
And so ends the journey of a girl who \n fell from the sky and changed the world...
